```
Fix: DexRouter contract ContractTrapped on quote calls

The getAmountOut function trapped when called via eth_call. Root cause: the PVM contract macro (pvm_contract_macros) uses the Rust parameter type to select the ABI decoder. Vec<u8> maps to Solidity uint8[] (each element padded to 32 bytes), but the Solidity interface declares bytes (length-prefixed packed encoding). When a 5-byte SCALE-encoded asset identifier arrived, the decoder tried to read 5 elements at 32-byte intervals from a single 32-byte word, causing an out-of-bounds memory access that trapped the PVM.

Solution: Changed all bytes parameters from Vec<u8> to pvm_contract_types::Bytes, and bytes[] parameters from Vec<Vec<u8>> to Vec<Bytes>. The Bytes type implements SolDecode with the correct packed-bytes decoder matching Solidity's bytes ABI encoding.

Additionally discovered that #[cfg_attr(not(test), pvm_contract_macros::method)] does not work inside a proc-macro-attributed module — cfg_attr on inner items is not expanded before the outer attribute macro receives the token stream. Removed the cfg_attr wrappers since the standalone method/constructor/fallback macros are identity transforms (they pass the function through unchanged when not consumed by the contract module macro).
```

